      "comment": "NANGAR LADY (1) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 7th at this track following on from a third place finish (34.84) there the start prior. Has a good record here at this journey. Better than last start and worth following up. BLACK CHIP (7) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close second, 1.5 lengths from the winner Regal Barry (30.75) at this track. Must be included in calculations. SCARY EYES (2) copped a check in the run and finished a well held 8 lengths seventh (22.85) last time in a Grade 5 at Murray Bridge over 395m. Can do much better this time. WOODSIDE FRANKIE (5) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
